Recommendations:
We recommended and the Municipal Mayor agreed that the:
Municipal Planning and Development Office, Municipal Engineering Office, as well as other Offices concerned such as the end-users collectively prepare a holistic and comprehensive yet realistic catch-up plan to expedite the project implementation of these funded projects which are still pending;
Municipal Engineering Office prepare the related Program of Works of PPAs in advance prior to its inclusion in the Annual Investment Plan to facilitate efficient implementation and monitoring;
Municipal Planning and Development Office ensure that all PPAs for infrastructure projects included in the Annual Investment Plan has corresponding Program of Works to facilitate efficient monitoring; and
Municipal Mayor continue to prioritize the implementation of the projects/programs/activities outlined in the AIP for the calendar year.

We recommended and Management agreed to:
Conduct proper validation of identified or proposed projects to ensure that only feasible and well-planned and procurement-and-implementation-ready PPAs, thus free from any issues of ownership and right-of-way or boundary issues, are included in the AIP;
Require the Municipal Planning and Development Office, in coordination with the other offices in the Municipality, to conduct initial re-assessment as to the viability of the planned projects prior years projects under the 20% Development Fund and provide recommendation to the Municipal Development Office if whether it is feasible to continue the project; and
Subsequently, coordinate with the Municipal Development Council to determine the appropriate action to be undertaken in relation to the recommendation of the MPDO as to the viability of the prior years; projects, particularly as to whether it is feasible to continue the projects or identify new programs, projects and activities to be implemented;

Recommendations:
We recommended and Management agreed on the following:
Instruct the Municipal Health Office (MHO) and the Municipal Environment and Natural Resources Office (MENRO) to develop a waste management plan to be implemented in the LIGTAS COVID-19 Center;
Instruct the MHO and MENRO to provide for the necessary specifications required in the COVID-19  facility infrastructures;
Require the Municipal Engineering Office to provide for: (a) a construction plan duly considering the specifications submitted by the Municipal Health Office; (b) total estimated cost for the waste management storage facility; (c) the submission of PPMP to the Bids and Awards Committee intended for the procurement of materials if available funds are identified; and,
Require the BAC to facilitate the expeditious procurement of the needed materials for the construction if the appropriate funding source was identified and made available.

Recommendations:
We recommended and Management agreed on the following:
Establish a Composite Team in the Local Solid Waste Management Board (LSWMB) that will take charge in the development of policies pertaining to COVID-19 related health care wastes and for its implementation;
Require the Municipal Environment and Natural Resources Officer (MENDRO) and LSWMB to prepare a COVID-19 waste management plan and integrate the same to the 10- year Solid Waste Management Plan of the Municipality;
Direct the MENRO to conduct orientation and other information drive about the proper management of COVID-19 related wastes in barangays; and,
Require the MENRO and the Composite Team to devise activities to support the Barangay Ecological Solid Waste Management Committees in the proper handling of COVID-19 related health care wastes.

Once again, we recommended the Municipal Mayor to:
• Consider to hire/assign additional member/s to the Inventory Committee to assist in the conduct of physical count of PPE;
• Instruct the Inventory Team to start the inventory taking as early as June 2020; complete the physical count of PPE accounts within a specified time; stick tags in each of the PPE;
• Require the Inventory Committee to prepare the Report on the Physical Count of Property, Plant and Equipment (RPCPPE); copy furnished the Accounting Office for reference; and submit copy to the COA Office; and
• Require the GSO and the Accountant to maintain property records; reconcile their respective property records and, make necessary adjustments if necessary.

1. Fast track the completion of the above-named projects. Regularly monitor the status of implementation; 
2. Plan all procurement activities judiciously to avoid the incurrence of the above-mentioned deficiencies pertaining to procurement activities; and
3. Before entering into another Memorandum of Agreement, Management should see to it that it has the capacity to implement the project within the time agreed upon by evaluating first all the aspects of the projects including procurement activities and technical capability to avoid delays in implementation.
